Well, welcome to the world of the chanter with 55+ Mobs.<br>
<br>
First, GoK, Rapture (level 59 - It is unresistable, I have mezzed Dark Reavers in CoM with it.) and Apathy (level 61) become your friends.  There is another mezz at level 64 (Bliss I think).<br>
<br>
Over time crowd control changes.  Slow becomes the primary damage mitigation tool.  Mezz gets trickier.  Its always good to try to mezz new mobs while you have 1 (for example some Giants in PoS are mezzable).  That way you can try mezz and root while your mates are beating on it.  FD pullers are more important and a mage with CoH really helps (CoH clears aggro).<br>
<br>
As for Firebone Casters, they are mezzable.  I can not recall if GoK can get them, but Rapture and Apathy can.  I have gotten a CoD flag from killing Grummus and I can not recall an unmezzable (non-named) mob along the way.  <br>
<br>
So how does one survive at level 60+?  Slow and Arcane Rune.  If a mob is slowed, I can take several hits in PoV (perhaps even re-rune).  There Apathy is the only mezz that works (and Rapture would be so useful too).<br>
<br>
So what to do if pulling unslowable mobs?  DoT/Tash is about the only useful thing we can do.  Those mobs need to go down fast, so anything that improves that damage output of the group is very handy.<br>
<br>
So, the competition for high level groups is Shaman.  Their slow and buffs are generally better than ours.  Chanters Haste is better and we can mezz many mobs even in higher planes.  Given the low DPS of each class (unless you are charming), it is rare that Chanters and Shaman group together.  Adds are very dangerous in Tier 2 planes as they hit hard and while mezzing one the other is unslowed.  2 unslowed Tier 2 mobs will take out most groups.<br>
<br>
Cames Houdini<br>
Level 63 Chanter - Vazelle<br>
