<br>
Pre GoK mezzes will not work on 56+ mobs.<br>
GoK works up to 57<br>
Rapture(59) works up to 61, and is unresistable (-1000 adjust)<br>
Apathy(61) up to 62, Sleep(63) up to 65 and Bliss(64) up to 67.<br>
GoK, Apathy, Sleep, Bliss all have -10 resist adjust and last 54 seconds.   Good technique is to first nail mob with Rapture, follow with Tash, and use a different mez after this, keeping Rapture available.<br>
<br>
None of our pre-60 stuns work on 56+ mobs.  This includes Color line, Largarn, and Nuke stun component.<br>
At 62, there is Word of Morrell, which is the ultimate Color series spell, and will stun all way up to 65.  Handy to interrupt Gates and CHs.<br>
<br>
Pacify will not work on 56+ mobs.<br>
Wake of Tranquility will work on mobs up to 60.  Good for splitting Guardians in PoD castle.<br>
Pacification(62) will pacify a 65 mob.  VERY useful spell.<br>
<br>
Do not forget alternatives to mez.  Fetter(5<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  is an awesome spell.   It is your fastest root, and it is cheap.  Guardians of the Crypt in PoD castle are unmezzable.   But root one away from party, and it's as good as mezzed.  Greater Fetter(61) is even better, thanks to its -30 resist adjust.<br>
<br>
At 59, my CC line up in PoD used to be GoK/Rapture/Fetter/MemFlux/Wake of Tranquility/Tashanian.<br>
<br>
At 61, it is<br>
Apathy/Rapture/GFetter/MemFlux/WoT/HoT<br>
<br>
Once I hit 62:<br>
Apathy/Rapture/GFetter/MemFlux/Pacification/HoT/Morrell. <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Bregalad Alcarin</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, High Elf Phantasmist, Xev &lt;Legends of Westwood&gt;<br>
