Couple of note to your spell list.<br>
<br>
First off, I think you missed 2 very important spells.  These are Boggle and Horrifying Visage.<br>
<br>
For anyone in the Planes, its quite common for Warrior MAs to have problems with Aggro Control.  Horrifying Visage helps that immeasurably.<br>
<br>
I use Boggle over Memflux all day long.  Casting Memflux has 3 issues: Its Uncertain, It wipes the whole aggro list, and it has a long cast and recast time.  Boggle has none of these issues.  Boggle is either resisted or not.  It takes you down on the hate list and is very very fast.<br>
<br>
Some mobs can not be lulled independent of level.  So I concur with your points on WoT and Pacification, but there are limits to there effectiveness.<br>
<br>
Rapture is overlooked as well by many chanters.  With it you can mezz anything that is mezzable with that spell, including Dark Reavers in CoM.  However, its generally ineffective in Tier 2 zones.<br>
<br>
Cames Houdini<br>
Level 63 Chanter - Vazelle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=megalythfreeheart>Megalyth Freeheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#330000>(4/13/03 12:38:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=173.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PoD mobs</span><hr size=1> I agree with Astyd on Boggle &amp; Horrifying Visage - HV used to be thought of as mainly a raid-use spell, when you have several tanks competing with the MT for dmg and so forth (geez, the testosterone on raids). :P<br>
<br>
BUT, here's a scenario I'm seeing more and more in the upper planes:  Group consists of Cleric, Chanter, and 4 dmg. dealers.  I'm on slows when there's no shammy present, so guess who's getting aggro?  Toss HV on the MT first, then hit your slow, and you can often go unnoticed by Mr. Ugly.<br>
<br>
If he DOES aggro you, Boggle casts in about 1/3rd or 1/4th the time blur does, and since all you did was bump yourself down his hate list (instead of wiping his list competely), all the aggro your MT worked so hard rises to the surface.<br>
<br>
Horryfying Visage &amp; Boggle really do make a fine pair. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
